contact_name: Publications Office of the European Union
description: The Languages name authority list (NAL) or Common Authority Table (CAT) is a controlled vocabulary listing languages with their authority code and label(s) in the 24 official languages of the EU (when available). The list is based on the ISO 639 standards and provides mappings between them. The Languages NAL is part of the Core Metadata (CM) used in the data exchange between the institutions involved in the legal decision making process and the Publications Office of the EU. The NAL is under governance of the Interinstitutional Metadata Maintenance Committee (IMMC) and maintained  by the Publications Office of the EU in its Metadata Registry (MDR)
title: Languages Name Authority List
name: language
contact_address: Publications Office of the EU; Core Business Services directorate; Enterprise Architecture, Methods and Formats unit; Formats, Linguistic Informatics and Metadata section; 2, rue Mercier; L-2985 Luxembourg
